The '''Taiwan rosefinch''' ('''''Carpodacus formosanus''''') is a species of [[finch]] in the family [[Fringillidae]].  It was formerly considered a subspecies of the [[vinaceous rosefinch]]. It is endemic to Taiwan. Its natural [[habitat]]s are temperate forests and subtropical or tropical dry forests.

